Maybe I&#x27;m misunderstanding you, but why wouldn&#x27;t it work in an expression based language?<p>Isn&#x27;t<p><pre><code>  if let pat = expr1 { expr2 }
</code></pre>
just syntactic sugar for<p><pre><code>  match expr1 {
    pat => { expr2 }
    _ => { }
</code></pre>
meaning the type of expr2 must be unit, and thusly if let is always of unit type?
